\nNo words were discarded as gibberish or unfixable. All input strings were recognized as valid Amharic or foreign proper nouns/loanwords.\n\n**PROTOCOL 3: THE CORRECTOR (Visual Repair)**\nNo significant OCR errors requiring visual repair were detected in this batch. Punctuation was not present in the input.\n\n**PROTOCOL 4: THE LEMMATIZER (Global Citation Form)**\nFor each cleaned word, the base dictionary entry (infinitive for verbs, singular/base form for nouns/adjectives) was identified. For instance, 'ቻለችው' (she was able) was lemmatized to 'መቻል' (to be able), 'ቻይናዊያን' (Chinese people) to 'ቻይናዊ' (Chinese person), 'ኀጥአን' (sinners) to 'ኀጥአተኛ' (sinner), and 'ኃለኞች' (the last ones) to 'ኃለኛ' (last/latter).\n\n**PROTOCOL 5: THE TRANSLATOR (Nuance Expansion)**\nComprehensive English synonyms were provided for each root, aiming to capture the full semantic breadth.\n\n**PROTOCOL 6: THE GRAMMARIAN (Linguistic Tagging)**\nEach word was assigned its appropriate Part of Speech (POS), such as Noun, Verb, Adjective, or Proper Noun.\n\n**PROTOCOL 7: THE FILTER (Size Constraint)**\nAll extracted words and roots met the minimum length requirement of two characters; no single-character entries were found or generated.\n\n**PROTOCOL 8: EXECUTIVE SUMMARY (Scholarly Guesses)**\n*   **Proper Nouns/Loanwords**: Words like 'ቺሻሚሶ', 'ቺፕ', 'ቻርሊ', 'ቻርተርድ', 'ቻይን', 'ቼልሲ', 'ቺካጎ', 'ቾዉበሪ', and 'ቾውበሪ' were identified as proper nouns or direct loanwords from English, and their roots were considered to be the words themselves.\n*   **Morphological Analysis**: The 'የ' prefix and various suffixes ('ን', 'ም', 'ና', 'ስ', 'ውን', 'ቹ', 'ህን') were consistently removed to isolate the core word for cleaning and lemmatization, reflecting standard Amharic morphological processes. For example, 'የቻለችውነ' was cleaned to 'ቻለችው' and lemmatized to 'መቻል', with 'ን' being an object marker. Similarly, 'የችግረኞችህን' was cleaned to 'ችግረኞች' and lemmatized to 'ችግረኛ'.\n*   **Plural to Singular Root**: For plural forms like 'ኀጥአን' and 'ኃያላን', the singular base forms 'ኀጥአተኛ' and 'ኃያል' were used as roots, respectively. Similarly, 'ችግረኞች' was rooted to 'ችግረኛ'.\n*   **Importance Scores**: Scores were assigned based on the general utility and commonality of the word, with core concepts and common nouns/verbs receiving higher scores, and specific proper nouns receiving slightly lower scores.","input_words":["የቺሻሚሶ","የቺፕ","የቻለችውነ","የቻርሊን","የቻርተርድ","የቻይናዊያንን","የቻይንን","የቼልሲተጫዋች","የችል","የችንካሩን","የችካጎ","የችጋረኛውን","የችግረኛም","የችግረኛን","የችግረኛውንም","የችግረኛውንና","የችግረኞችህን","የቾዉበሪ","የቾውበሪ","የኀጥአንን","የኀጥአንንም","የኀጥኣንን","የኃለኞቹ","የኃያላንም","የኃያላንንም","የኃይሉና","የኃይሉንስ","የኃይላችሁን","የኃይላችሁንም","የኃይልህም"],"batch_number":null,"batch_label":null,"model_version":"gemini-2.5-flash"},{"id":"fb840244-e3e8-4a24-91ff-fb7f9f906eeb","created_at":"2026-03-02T13:22:15.008954+00:00","word":null,"source_file":"rare_words_25/chunk_0359.txt","batch_index":0,"words":[{"pos":"Verb","root":"መነጠቅ","word":"የነጠቃትን","synonyms":["to snatch","to seize","to plunder","to rob","to take away by force"],"importance":5},{"pos":"Verb","root":"መጥፋት","word":"የነጠፋባቸውን","synonyms":["to be lost","to disappear","to be erased","to vanish"],"importance":5},{"pos":"Verb","root":"መነጣጠል","word":"የነጣጠለ","synonyms":["to separate","to divide","to disunite","to fragment"],"importance":5},{"pos":"Noun","root":"ነጭነት","word":"የነጭነትን","synonyms":["whiteness","purity","fairness","innocence"],"importance":5},{"pos":"Proper Noun","root":"ነጸጋዬ","word":"የነጸጋዬን","synonyms":["Netsegaye"],"importance":5},{"pos":"Adjective","root":"ነጻ","word":"የነጻውም","synonyms":["free","independent","liberated","autonomous"],"importance":5},{"pos":"Noun","root":"ነጻነት","word":"የነፃት","synonyms":["freedom","liberty","independence"],"importance":5},{"pos":"Verb","root":"መነፈግ","word":"የነፈገችው","synonyms":["to deny","to refuse","to withhold","to deprive"],"importance":5},{"pos":"Verb","root":"መነፈግ","word":"የነፈጉኝን","synonyms":["to deny","to refuse","to withhold","to deprive"],"importance":5},{"pos":"Verb","root":"